  "response": "Money laundering prosecution involves complex legal challenges, including:\n\n1. Evidence Collection Challenges\n- Sophisticated financial transaction tracing\n- International jurisdictional complexities\n- Technical digital transaction tracking\n- Complex financial record analysis\n\n2. Legal Jurisdictional Issues\n- Cross-border transaction investigations\n- Different international legal frameworks\n- Varying money laundering definitions\n- Extradition limitations\n\n3. Procedural Obstacles\n- High burden of proof requirements\n- Demonstrating intentional criminal conduct\n- Technical financial evidence interpretation\n- Establishing direct criminal connection\n\n4. Technological Complications\n- Cryptocurrency anonymity\n- Dark web transaction obfuscation\n- Rapidly evolving digital financial technologies\n- Encrypted communication challenges\n\n5. Investigative Constraints\n- Limited financial forensic expertise\n- Resource-intensive investigations\n- Complex multinational coordination\n- Advanced concealment techniques\n\n6. Legal Defense Strategies\n- Complex financial transaction arguments\n- Technical legal challenges\n- Professional expert testimony\n- Constitutional privacy protections\n\nThese challenges require sophisticated legal, technological, and investigative approaches to successfully prosecute money laundering offenses.",
